parameters:
Researcher Caron: We can't do anything without first
securing the dispatch of advanced sorcerers.

Researcher Caron: The airship was amazing. I'll use it as a
reference for my next research paper!
Researcher Caros: Sorry for being busy!

Mage Relm: I've been relying on you, so I heard you want to
investigate the Eastern-style costumes.

Researcher Caros: I heard that you obtained something at the
Great Rock Castle, so I thought there might be a hint for my
research.

Mage Relm: If that's the case, please let me prepare a
little.

Researcher Caros: Oh my... I can't investigate what you're
wearing, as expected.

Researcher Caros: Thank you! It seems like it's made with
technology that the Empire doesn't have.

Researcher Caros: ...I heard that the girl who was wearing
it went berserk, is that true?

Mage Relm: It was terrible! If I hadn't destroyed the
crystal, I would have been completely defeated.
Researcher Caros: You destroyed the crystal...?

Mage Relm: Actually, I was absorbing magic power from the
crystal. Maybe that's the original way to use it.

Researcher Caros: It's interesting to come up with something
that assumes the preparation of magic power from the
outside, even though we don't know who made it.

Researcher Caros: If you're willing, could you show me how
you absorb magic power from the crystal?
Mage Relm: That would be quite a dangerous experiment...

Researcher Caros: I'll use this tiny crystal! It seems like
it could lead to new ideas, just like this!

Mage Relm: Haa, understood. Please make sure to help me when
I'm in trouble, okay?

Researcher Caros: Of course! Now, let's conduct the
experiment in the underground laboratory.

Researcher Caros: When you're ready... let me know when
you're wearing the Eastern-style outfit.
Researcher Caros: Alright, it looks like we're ready.
Researcher Caros: Alright, let's conduct the experiment.

Researcher Caros: This time, it's important to wear the
ceremonial attire from the Far East. Make sure to put it on
before we begin.

Researcher Caron: I apologize for the reckless experiment. I
will refrain from doing it again.

Researcher Caron: The airship was amazing. I will use it as
a reference for my next research paper!

Researcher Caron: I'm sorry to say this, but the research
that Dokusa-kun was talking about has been frozen due to
some issues with the client.
Researcher Caron: I'm sorry, but I can't be of any help.

Clea: Is there some kind of problem? I came to see you to
resolve the issue.

Researcher Caron: The cost and personnel are the first major
issues. We would have to use the gigantic crystal almost as
a disposable resource.

Researcher Caron: To control the ship, we would need
multiple advanced mages. I'm not sure about the size of the
ship, but it wouldn't be able to fly for more than an hour.

Clea: I may not understand the complicated details, but is
it possible to just make the ship float?

Researcher Caron: If we limit it to that... isn't it some
kind of military request?

Clea: I think it's just within the realm of hobbies. The
preparation of the gigantic crystal is complete.

Researcher Caron: In that case...! No, there's no way they
would dispatch advanced mages for a hobby.
Clea: Who should I talk to?

Researcher Caron: We need permission from the highest
authority of the Magic Academy, the Archmage.

Researcher Caron: If we can dispatch advanced mages, I would
like to participate in the development of the airship.

Magic Academy Researcher: Ah, so busy, so busy! Everyone is
too rough with people!
Magic Academy Researcher: That is a crystal for experiments!
Mage Relm: That was quite a hassle, seriously...

Magic Academy Researcher: Thank you very much! This is a
token of appreciation, so please accept it.

Magic Academy Researcher: Ah, so busy, so busy! Everyone is
too rough with people!

Intermediate male magician: Why does the room get dirty when
research progresses... Could it be that you came to help
with the cleaning... Oh, wait, that's not it, is it?

Male Intermediate Mage: I heard about your purpose. Give up
on foolish things and help me clean the room, will you?

Intermediate male sorcerer: I heard about the dragon
subjugation. Asking me to clean the room is not something
you can joke about.

Male Junior Sorcerer: I'm completely in a slump... I need
some excitement.

Male Junior Sorcerer: What beauty...! I'm feeling motivated,
I want you to take this.
Male Junior Magician: I'm feeling motivated!

Mage Relm: Well, that's true... but it's a subject outside
of my expertise, so it's quite difficult...

Mage Relm: But since I've made such a bold statement, and
for the honor of the Magic Academy, I will definitely
complete it!
Mage Relm: Ugh! It's not going well at all!

Mage Relm: It's so troublesome... and the recipes I received
are hardly useful...
Mage Relm: It's not like me to become so pessimistic.

Mage Relm: Let's take a break and get some fresh air to
clear our minds.
Advanced Mage: Aren't you all... the famous Dragon Slayers!

Clea: There's something I'd like to ask for your cooperation
as researchers from the Academy.

Advanced Mage: If it's for the sake of the Academy, I will
do my best to cooperate.
Advanced Mage: I see, creating needles based on gold, huh...

Thief Nora: I-Is it difficult...? It's absolutely necessary
for Docsa-san's sake!

Advanced Mage: If you're acquaintances of Docsa-san, how
about I sell you gold at a discounted price?

Advanced Mage: Sorry, but I also need it for my research, so
I can't give it to you any cheaper than this.

Advanced Mage: If you can gather the money and come back,
I'm sorry but I can't just give it to you for free.

Advanced Mage: If you have this amount, would it be enough?
I think it's a cheap price considering our comrades from the
Academy.

Thief Nora: Thank you very much! So Docsa-san isn't just a
weird person after all!

Advanced Mage: Haha, there's no doubt that Docsa-san is a
weird person, but more than that, they're someone who loves
the Magic Academy.

Advanced Mage: I don't know what it will be used for, but
I'm praying for the success of the experiment.

Mage Relm: We have the materials... now we just need to find
someone who can process them with high precision.

Mage Relm: Yes, that's true... Docsa-san seems to know a lot
of people.

Advanced Mage: I don't know what it will be used for, but
I'm praying for the success of the experiment.
